  <h1>
   time_source_stop
  </h1>
  This function stops the given
  <span>
   Time Source
  </span>
  and resets its timer.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">time_source_stop(id);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <colgroup>
    <col/>
    <col/>
    <col/>
   </colgroup>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      id
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Time_Sources/time_source_create.htm">
        Time Source ID
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The
      <span>
       Time Source
      </span>
      to stop
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">if (time_source_get_state(time_source) != time_source_state_stopped)
{
    time_source_stop(time_source);
}
</code></pre>
  The code above will stop a
  <span>
   Time Source
  </span>
  when it's not already stopped.
 </body>
